    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>eo</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>I</abbr><ex>nvicto</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>ithrae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>auti</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>itus</ex></expan> Flavius <lb n="3"/>Verecundus <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>Cl</abbr><ex>audia</ex></expan> Savaria <lb n="5"/>|(centurio) <expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ionis</ex></expan> XIIII <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>g</abbr><ex>eminae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>artiae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>ictricis</ex></expan> <lb n="7"/><expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>otum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>olvit</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibens</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>aetus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erito</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Auf der linken Nebenseite Cautopates, auf der rechten Cautes. Reste von roter Farbe in den Buchstaben. Z. 3: Buchstabe S steht auf dem Rahmen. Laut Kremer ist Z. 1: C(autopati?) wegen der ausgeschriebenen Parallelen wahrscheinlicher.</p>
            </div>
